    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 23.54,
      "end": 26.26,
      "text": "ASOP's Fables, The Wolf and the Lion.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 26.26,
      "end": 34.66,
      "text": "A wolf stole a lamp from the flock and was carrying it off to devour it at his leisure,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 35.46,
      "end": 41.1,
      "text": "when he met a lion, who took his prey away from him and walked off with it.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 41.74,
      "end": 48.9,
      "text": "He dared not resist, but when the lion had gone some distance, he said,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 48.9,
      "end": 55.28,
      "text": "it is most unjust of you to take what's mine away from me like that.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 56.64,
      "end": 61.12,
      "text": "But the lion laughed and called out in reply.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 62.18,
      "end": 65.14,
      "text": "It was justly yours, no doubt.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 65.96,
      "end": 69.82,
      "text": "The gift of a friend, perhaps, aye?",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-013",
      "start": 70.92,
      "end": 73.38,
      "text": "End of The Wolf and the Lion.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
